&reftitle.description;
arrayfalsecubrid_batch_execute resourceconn_identifier arraysql_stmt
The cubrid_batch_execute function executes several SQL statements in a single batch, over the connection given by conn_identifier. It is intended for data manipulation statements (such as INSERT, UPDATE or DELETE).

  &reftitle.examples;

   cubrid_batch_execute example


<?php
$conn = cubrid_connect('localhost', 33000, 'demodb');

$result = cubrid_batch_execute($conn, [
    "INSERT INTO game (event_code) VALUES (20001)",
    "INSERT INTO game (event_code) VALUES (20002)",
    "UPDATE game SET event_code = 20003 WHERE event_code = 20001",
]);

var_dump($result);

cubrid_disconnect($conn);
?>
